# conanxin-homepage — Taste Rules

**Reference DNA**: Vercel (primary — engineering clarity, restraint) + Linear (secondary — dark theme, tool-over-display) + Stripe (local accent only — single-accent discipline, NOT marketing-page moves).
**Source audit**: `outputs/taste-3a-conanxin-homepage-audit/TASTE_3A_HOMEPAGE_DESIGN_AUDIT.md` (in the taste-lab-pilot repo).
**Full design rationale**: `docs/homepage-taste-rules.md` (in this repo).

---

## Identity

Personal digital-garden home. Terminal / code-editor aesthetic. The interface feels like a calm, restrained entry point — not a marketing page, not a dashboard. Single-page, multi-section. Dark theme only. The monospace font is the identity.

## Color tokens (use these; never hardcode hex outside `styles/main.css :root`)

```
--bg-primary: #0d1117             (page + body, near-black with cool blue cast)
--bg-secondary: #161b22          (status bar, surface cards)
--bg-tertiary: #21262d           (elevated surface, scrollbar thumb)
--text-primary: #e6edf3          (headings, key labels)
--text-secondary: #8b949e        (body copy)
--text-muted: #6e7681            (timestamps, low-emphasis)
--accent-green: #7ee787          (PRIMARY accent — links, active states, "Now" highlight, focus)
--accent-blue: #79c0ff           (SECONDARY accent — secondary interactive text)
--border-color: #30363d          (1px borders, dividers)
```

## Accent rationing (mandatory — 1+1 discipline)

`--accent-green` / `#7ee787`: links, active nav items, focus-visible outline, status dot, "Now" section highlight. **Nothing else.**
`--accent-blue` / `#79c0ff`: secondary interactive text. **Nothing else.**

**No other accent colors.** P0 removed 3 unused accent tokens (`--accent-orange`, `--accent-purple`, `--accent-red`) to enforce this discipline structurally. Do not re-add them.

Never: section headers in accent, dividers in accent, decorative icons in accent, card decorations in accent, multiple accent elements competing for attention, decorative use of accent on backgrounds.

Before merging, run `grep -rE '#7ee787|var\(--accent-green\)' styles/` and `grep -rE '#79c0ff|var\(--accent-blue\)' styles/` — if either count grew beyond the legitimate uses above, accent crept in.

## Typography

- **Font family**: `'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', 'Consolas', monospace` (web font via Google Fonts CDN; system-mono fallback chain is required)
- **2 font weights only**: `400` and `600`. No `300`, no `500`, no `700`, no `900`.
- **Scale** (already in use):
  - Hero title: `28px` / `600` (deliberately small — terminal aesthetic, not marketing-page scale)
  - H2: `20px` / `600` / line-height `28px`
  - H3: `16px` / `600` / line-height `22.4px`
  - Body: `16px` / `400` / line-height `27.2px` (1.7×)
  - Meta: `14px` / `400`
- **No H1 element** — the homepage uses a `<div class="logo">`. Don't change to `<h1>` without author review.
- **No negative letter-spacing** — monospace fonts are already balanced.
- **No web font addition** — JetBrains Mono (via Google Fonts) is the only one. Don't add Inter, Geist, IBM Plex, etc. (Inter was loaded but unused; P0 dropped it.)

## Spacing scale (use these values)

```
--space-xs: 0.25rem   (4px — base unit × 1)
--space-sm: 0.5rem    (8px)
--space-md: 1rem      (16px)
--space-lg: 1.5rem    (24px)
--space-xl: 2rem      (32px)
--space-xxl: 3rem     (48px — section gap)
```

No `64px`, no `96px`, no other values.

## Container & grid

- **Max-width**: `800px` (via `--max-width`; do NOT change to 1440px or 1280px)
- **Body padding**: terminal-container has its own padding; the wide side margins ARE the whitespace
- **Grid**: 2 columns in `.featured-grid`, 24px gutter, `repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr))` for responsiveness

## Components

### Status bar
- Top of viewport, full width (within terminal-container), ~32px height
- Background: `var(--bg-secondary)` (`#161b22`)
- Text: `var(--text-muted)`
- Status dot: 8px circle in `var(--accent-green)`, with `pulse` keyframe animation (2s infinite)
- Right side: version / datetime, all monospace, all muted

### Nav
- Horizontal flex with `.terminal-nav` class
- Item padding via `--space-md` and `--space-sm`
- Default: muted text → hover: green accent → active: primary text + green underline
- Numbered prefix (`01.`, `02.`, etc.) in muted color

### Card / featured item
- Background: `var(--bg-secondary)`
- Border: `1px solid var(--border-color)`
- Radius: `var(--border-radius)` (6px) for cards; 4px for chips
- **Shadow: NONE** (flat depth discipline)
- Hover: `border-color` shifts only; no lift, no shadow change, no scale

### Button / link
- Background: transparent
- Text: `var(--text-secondary)` default → `var(--accent-green)` on hover
- Padding: minimal (terminal aesthetic)
- Border: none

## Transitions

- **Properties**: `color` and `border-color` only (NOT `transform`, NOT `opacity`, NOT `box-shadow`)
- **Duration**: `0.2s`
- **Easing**: `ease` (default)

The transition discipline is part of the terminal aesthetic. Adding `transform: scale(1.05)` on hover would break the terminal feel.

## Accessibility (MANDATORY — ship in P0)

1. **`:focus-visible` outline rule** — 2px solid `var(--accent-green)`, 2px offset, 4px border-radius. Closes WCAG 2.4.7.
2. **`prefers-reduced-motion` media query** — kills all transitions, animations, and the `.status-dot` pulse animation when user has reduced-motion set. Closes WCAG 2.3.3.
3. **Color contrast** — all current text/bg pairs above WCAG AA (verified in TASTE-3A audit §9).

## Mobile (below 768px)

- Container: full-width (no 800px constraint)
- Nav: collapse to single horizontal scroll row (`.terminal-nav` flex-wrap)
- Grid: collapse to single column
- Touch targets: min 44×44px
- Font sizes: stay the same (system font scaling handles the rest)

## Anti-patterns (always forbidden)

- Hero image
- Light theme
- Multi-color accent expansion (the 1+1 discipline is sacred)
- `filter: drop-shadow(...)`
- Multi-layer shadows (zero shadows is the discipline)
- Gradients (zero gradients is the discipline)
- Pill-shape buttons (radius 4-6px is the discipline; chips stay 4px)
- Hover lift above 1px
- Animations on text content (only `color` and `border-color` may transition)
- Box-shadow on cards
- SaaS-hero layout (big headline + subhead + CTA)
- Web font addition beyond JetBrains Mono
- Proportional font families in any selector (everything must be monospace)
- Container > 800px
- Bento grid / asymmetric mosaic
- Direct use of `#7ee787` in component CSS (use `var(--accent-green)`)
- Direct use of `#79c0ff` in component CSS (use `var(--accent-blue)`)
- Direct use of `#0d1117` in component CSS (use `var(--bg-primary)`)
- `git add .` / `git add -A` (per-file add is mandatory; the repo has many `projects/*` sub-directories)

## 4 extracted taste principles (read these first)

1. **Monospace as Identity** — JetBrains Mono for every text role; the monospace aesthetic IS the site's personality
2. **Flat Depth Over Simulated Depth** — zero shadows, zero gradients; cards separated only by 1-step background contrast and 1px border
3. **Sparse Canvas Over Data Density** — 800px container on 1440px viewport (~55% width); the whitespace signals "there's no rush"
4. **One Accent, Used with Discipline** — `#7ee787` for active states only; `#79c0ff` for secondary interactive; nothing else

## P0 scope (TASTE-3B; do only these in P0)

1. Add `:focus-visible` outline rule
2. Add `prefers-reduced-motion` media query
3. Remove 3 unused accent colors (`--accent-orange`, `--accent-purple`, `--accent-red`)
4. Migrate `.featured-date` and `.post-date` from `var(--accent-orange)` to `var(--text-muted)`
5. Drop Inter from the Google Fonts URL
6. Remove unused `--font-sans` token
7. Add `docs/homepage-taste-rules.md` (design rationale)
8. Add this file (`.cursor/rules/conanxin-homepage-taste.mdc`)
9. Extend top-level `CLAUDE.md` with the "Conanxin Homepage Taste Rules (TASTE-3B)" section

## P1 scope (defer to TASTE-3C)

- Skip-to-main-content link
- Section IDs for direct linking
- Active-section highlighting in nav
- Image lazy-loading preparation

## P2 scope (defer to TASTE-3D)

- `scripts/check-design-tokens.sh` + `.github/workflows/design-lint.yml` for CI enforcement

## When in doubt

Read `docs/homepage-taste-rules.md` (in this repo) for the full rationale behind every rule. If a change doesn't fit any of the 4 documented principles, propose it as a separate design review — not a silent code change.
